* Compiling and installing loco-lingo
-------------------------------

    We will assume you want to install loco-lingo in /opt/KonicaMinolta.

    To compile loco-lingo type and install it to /opt/KonicaMinolta:

	./configure --prefix=/opt/KonicaMinolta
	make 
	make install

    If you don't specify --prefix, it will default to /opt/KonicaMinolta

    If ./configure finds a working 'gmcs' it will automatically build a
    2.0 profile version of xsp, named xsp2.

* Running loco-lingo 
------------------------------------

	mono /opt/KonicaMinolta/bin/loco-lingo-cli.exe 


Notes for MS runtime users
----------------------------
In windows, if you want to build xsp using csc, do:

    MCS=csc make
